communicated by:
ProMED

Data by country, area, or territory for 18 May 2022 can be accessed at
https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2022%20WHO%20Data%20Tables%20MAY18_1653021556.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 27.3% of cases and 24.9% of deaths during the past 24 hours having reported more than 155.09 million cases, second to the European region, as the most severely affected region. The USA reported 142 209 cases in the last 24 hours followed by Brazil, Chile, Panama, and Canada, all reporting more than 1000 cases. Aruba reported more than 500, but less than 1000 cases. Argentina, Mexico, Colombia, and Uruguay, among others, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The European region reported 36.6% of cases and 48.2% of deaths over the last 24 hours, as the most affected region, with cumulative cases exceeding 218.75 million. Some countries reporting few or no cases in the last 24 hours or longer include the UK, Portugal, Belgium, Ukraine, Switzerland (2 cases), Sweden, and Tajikistan. No country reported more than 100 000 cases. A total of 11 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours: 4 reported more than 10 000 cases and 7 reported over 1000 cases. 4 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 0.50% cases and 4.3% deaths during the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 21.74 million cases. Saudi Arabia (621) reported the highest number of cases followed by Bahrain and Tunisia. Overall, the reporting from the region has been low over the last few weeks, with many countries not reporting cases.

- The African region reported 0.96% cases and 2.7% deaths during the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.91 million cases. South Africa (5096) reported the highest number of cases. 36 countries/territories did not report any case over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 33.3% of daily case numbers and 13.8% deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 57.82 million cases. China (66 239) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Australia, Japan, South Korea, New Zealand, Singapore, Viet Nam, and Malaysia. [No cases are currently shown for North Korea (officially Democratic People's Republic of Korea). - Mod.SH]

- The South East Asia region reported 1.3% of the daily newly reported cases and 5.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 58.38 million cases. Thailand (5633) reported the highest number of cases followed by India (1829) and Indonesia (327). Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, and Myanmar, among others, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 18 May 2022, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

