[In the past 24 hours, 12 countries -- North Korea (262 280), USA (219 259), Taiwan (85 082), Germany (64 582), Australia (53 139), Japan (33 734), Italy (30 927), France (29 995), South Korea (28 105), Ireland (16 384), Brazil (13 525), and Costa Rica (11 369) -- all reported over 10 000 newly confirmed cases. A global total of 2168 deaths were reported in the preceding 24 hours (late 17 May 2022 to late 18 May 2022).

A total of 29 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 11 of the 29 countries are from the European region, 6 are from the Americas region, 0 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 8 are from the Western Pacific region, 3 from the South East Asia region, and 1 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 57.5%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 0.21%. Comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 23.8% increase in daily reported cases and a 0.04% increase in reported deaths. There is an overall global trend of decreasing cases and deaths.

Impression: Worldwide over 0.94 million newly confirmed infections were reported in the past 24 hours. The cumulative totals exceed 525.03 million reported cases and 6.29 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
